St. Porphyrios says it is best to try not to "imagine Christ" while praying to Him, as it is easy for us to make this mental image deformed by our own sentiments, or have it interfered with by something else, thus (partly) praying to an idol - better just look at an icon instead.

Saint Porphyrios also says that if a man keeps sinning and feels "trapped" in his life, instead of drowning in depression days at a time, one should "act like a man held captive by bandits" - out of the blue, JUMP and free yourself with an unexpected quick motion, go and run free

Saint Porphyrios says it is a mistake to pray only for yourself, because it is impossible to attain salvation alone - instead one should pray for his loved ones, acquaintances, for the entire world, hoping for others to be saved too and join into Heaven.
